<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/64881113-jami-mcginley"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/64881113-jami-mcginley">Jami McGinley</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I&apos;d say yes, but you might not have as much of an understanding of the many characters and what drives their choices. The second book does quickly rev<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I'd say yes, but you might not have as much of an understanding of the many characters and what drives their choices. The second book does quickly review important information from the first book, but briefly.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
