        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3250007777" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14790000137913778394">Many, many years ago I was introduced to the North and South book series by a television miniseries of the same name. It starred a young (and absolutely gorgeous) Patrick Swayze. <br/><br/>After watching the miniseries I knew I just had to read the books. Since then I have reread them many times and every time I was struck by the way John Jakes was able to convey the extreme emotionality of the Civil War Era. <br/><br/>If anyone has not yet read this book series, they need to add it to their TBR (To Be Read) list. </span>
  <span id="freeText14790000137913778394" style="display:none">Many, many years ago I was introduced to the North and South book series by a television miniseries of the same name. It starred a young (and absolutely gorgeous) Patrick Swayze. <br /><br />After watching the miniseries I knew I just had to read the books. Since then I have reread them many times and every time I was struck by the way John Jakes was able to convey the extreme emotionality of the Civil War Era. <br /><br />If anyone has not yet read this book series, they need to add it to their TBR (To Be Read) list. <br /><br />I rate NORTH AND SOUTH as 4 out of 5 Stars ⭐⭐⭐⭐</span>
