              <span id="reviewTextContainer689303811" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8731175863515509283">I love the North &amp; South trilogy and this book does not disappoint. I absolutely love how Jakes maintains historical accuracy while weaving the stories of his fictional characters into the history. He doesn&apos;t just do this with the major historical events, but with smaller details that we don&apos;t normally think of when we think of history. Jakes makes the era come alive. <br/><br/>While I also loved the TV miniseries for what it was (Patrick Swayze, after all), the books are better. <br/><br/>It is a very long book, b</span>
  <span id="freeText8731175863515509283" style="display:none">I love the North &amp; South trilogy and this book does not disappoint. I absolutely love how Jakes maintains historical accuracy while weaving the stories of his fictional characters into the history. He doesn't just do this with the major historical events, but with smaller details that we don't normally think of when we think of history. Jakes makes the era come alive. <br /><br />While I also loved the TV miniseries for what it was (Patrick Swayze, after all), the books are better. <br /><br />It is a very long book, but it's worth the time spent reading it. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8731175863515509283" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


